Use the editor below to calculate the following:   Let's say you bought five raffle tickets (out of the possible 100). Use the calculator notation to define the probability of a RaffleWin in this situation.  Then, on the next line, use the calculator notation to check what the probability is.  Use the calculator to calculate the probability of  not  winning the raffle, for the situation where you bought 5 raffle tickets.  Let's say that next Saturday is a typical day. Weather records show that 200 out of the last 1000 Saturdays had rain.  Use the calculator to calculate the chance of rain next Saturday.  Further to question 3, What is the probability of no rain?  Somebody says, "the project is unlikely to fail".  Assuming that "unlikely" means that only 20 out of 100 comparable projects have failed in the past, use the calculator to translate the sentence into a probability calculation.   

     Type your formulas below (don't forget the backticks) 


   activate_ckeditor("editor1","CalcButton");

In the example above, what is the chance of rain on both days of the weekend?  What is the probability of rain only on Saturday?   

