Assume that in the desert the following is the case. There is a 25% chance that your engine will overheat.  If the engine overheats, it is very likely (85%) that the overheating indicator will light up on your dashboard.    Show the probability variables and relationship a diagram  How can the given information be captured as probability statements?  What is the probability that the "overheating" indicator light will go on?   

     Type your formulas below (don't forget the backticks) 


   activate_ckeditor("editor1","CalcButton");

Imagine the following scenario: It is likely (80%) that illegal arms have been purchased in the city A. Smuggled goods from A are mostly (70%) shipped through city B, but sometimes (30%) through city C.  If the shipment is shipped through B, then there is an 80% chance that the arrival in city D will be noticed. If the goods are shipped through C, then the arrival will unlikely (20%) to be noticed in D.   Draw a diagram of the probability network of the above problem  Translate the problem into probability statements.  What is the percent chance that the arms shipment will be noticed in D?  What is the percent chance that illegal arms were purchased in Abalastat, if they are noticed in D? why?  What is the chance that illegal arms were shipped through B, given that they were noticed in D?   

     Type your formulas below (don't forget the backticks) 


